# -*- coding: utf-8; tab-width: 4; -*-
# ex: set fenc=utf-8 sts=4 ts=4 et nomod:

2023-07-21 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add cloudi_service_http_cowboy argument use_only_http2

2023-07-20 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Improve cloudi_service_http_cowboy HTTP/2 support
    * Update cowboy
    * Update cowlib

2023-07-19 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add cloudi_service_validate_config service to
      identify CloudI configuration inconsistencies

2023-07-04 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Improve Python/C CloudI API compilation

2023-07-03 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Improve Python/C CloudI API type usage for clang compilation,
      compiler optimization and portability
    * Add configuration validation to prevent
      the bind service configuration option from being used with
      the count_process_dynamic service configuration option to
      ensure bind is only used for static allocations of processes
      among logical processors

2023-06-29 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Remove nongnu-libunwind usage from the C++ backtrace
      functionality due to the instability it caused with
      gcc/g++ compilations with optimization level -O1 or higher
      using libunwind 1.2.1
      (libstdc++ uses the libgcc unwinder which created a SEGV
       if libunwind 1.2.1 was linked into the release build,
       if C++ throw was called very quickly for a long period of time)
    * Fix OCaml CloudI API compilation with parallel make

2023-06-28 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add m4/ax_cxx_stdlib.m4 for usage of LLVM libc++ as
      clang's stdlib (instead of the GCC libstdc++)
    * Update m4/ax_compiler_version.m4

2023-06-26 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix Python/C integration tests API class instantiation
      (so the Python CloudI API is not being used instead)
    * Add 2.0.6 release cloudi_service_request_rate results

2023-06-24 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix compiler warning

2023-06-21 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * CloudI version 2.0.6 released

2023-06-12 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Remove linux_setcap.sh modifications for the 'cgroup'
      external service configuration option because adding
      OS pids to a cgroup requires being root
        * Using 'cgroup' requires that CloudI was executed as root
    * Update cgroups

2023-06-08 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add the service configuration option 'critical' to
      cause the service to stop the CloudI node
      if the service fails, to escalate the failure
    * Improve the cloudi_service_shell interactive argument

2023-06-07 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add the interactive argument to cloudi_service_shell

2023-06-05 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Improve the Rust CloudI API
        * Add http_req integration test
    * Update cpg

2023-06-03 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add Rust CloudI API unwrap macro for callback ? functionality
    * Fix rust messaging test so it doesn't panic on termination
    * Add pid to the external service spawn error 
      (e.g. "OS pid PID spawn error ENUM")

2023-06-02 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Improve external service exit status log output when an error
      occurs during the fork-exec sequence in cloudi_os_spawn
      (e.g. "OS spawn error exec_ENOENT")
    * Fix pre-26.0 Erlang/OTP support that relies on individual
      OTP applications release directories without archive output
      (empty directories) that causes include_lib problems

2023-06-01 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Improve the Rust CloudI API
        * Removed the subscribe_mut function for using closures with a context
          due to the added latency, complexity and functionality problems it
          led to (unsubscribe functionality in a callback wasn't correct)

2023-05-31 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Improve the Rust CloudI API
        * Add subscribe_mut function for using closures with a context
        * Add messaging integration test

2023-05-30 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Improve the Rust CloudI API
        * Add null and msg_size integration tests
    * Fix external service exit status log output to always use
      integer output for values <= 128 instead of the
      C/C++ CloudI API enum names ("OS pid PID exited with INTEGER")

2023-05-26 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add the beginnings of a Rust CloudI API implementation

2023-05-20 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add Erlang/OTP 26.0 support
    * Update jinterface
    * Update erlang_go
    * Update erlang_hs
    * Update erlang_js
    * Update erlang_ml
    * Update erlang_pl
    * Update erlang_php
    * Update erlang_py
    * Update erlang_rb

2023-05-08 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add cloudi_service_cron support for random ranges with the
      ~ (tilde) character based on OpenBSD cron
    * Update quickrand

2023-03-27 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix average length of a Gregorian year constant
    * Improve ATS CloudI API function effect tags comment

2023-03-16 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add cloudi_service_map_reduce:map_size/0 function
    * Change the OCaml use of num-1.1 to zarith-1.12 for big-integer support
      in the Erlang External Term Format
    * Update erlang_ml
    * Update erlang_py

2023-03-14 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Update erlang_go

2023-03-03 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Change the C++ CloudI API backtrace dependency order selection
      to binutils, libdw, libdwarf
      (libdwarf functionality needs verification for libdwarf
       versions >= 20210528 that includes checking whether it
       provides more information)
    * Add to ATS CloudI API function effect tags comment

2023-02-21 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add bind service configuration option string value for providing
      the exact logical processors of the bind

2023-02-17 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add Java, JavaScript, OCaml, Perl, PHP, Python, Python/C, Ruby
      CloudI API functions for service process constant value access
      before CloudI API initialization:
        * timeout_initialize
        * timeout_terminate
        * process_index
        * process_count_max
        * process_count_min

2023-02-16 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add ATS, Go, Haskell CloudI API functions for service process
      constant value access before CloudI API initialization:
        * timeout_initialize
        * timeout_terminate
        * process_index
        * process_count_max
        * process_count_min

2023-02-15 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add C/C++ CloudI API functions for service process constant value
      access before CloudI API initialization:
        * timeout_initialize
        * timeout_terminate
        * process_index
        * process_count_max
        * process_count_min
    * Add Erlang/OTP 26.0-rc1 support

2023-02-14 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add bind service configuration option support for external service
      threads in the ATS, C/C++, Python/C CloudI API

2023-02-13 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add the bind service configuration option to bind
      CloudI service Erlang pids to scheduler threads
      if the schduler threads are bound
      (external service OS pid threads don't have their
       affinity set yet based on the bind option)

2023-02-10 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix external service stdout/stderr logging when the
      stdout/stderr data is 16KiB without any newlines

2023-02-09 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add CloudI Service API services_update pid options
      modifications for pids that are not restarted
      (info_pid_options when duo_mode == true and dispatcher_pid_options)

2023-02-08 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Improve cloudi_service_api_requests representations of
      aspect function lists to ensure only literal functions are
      encoded as string data
      (in the erl/json response of logging and services)
    * Allow CloudI Service API services_update to change
      info_pid_options when duo_mode == true to be like dispatcher_pid_options
      (the change is only able to occur after a restart)
    * Add support for the new async_dist erlang:spawn_opt/2 option
    * Update uuid

2023-01-07 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix CloudI Service API services_update options usage of
      request_pid_uses, request_pid_options, info_pid_uses,
      info_pid_options for internal services
    * Fix CloudI Service API services_update options validation of
      info_pid_uses and info_pid_options for internal services that
      have the duo_mode option set to true

2023-01-06 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix cloudi_service_api_requests json representations of
      aspect function lists to simplify the data as a single string and
      avoid the interpretation of Erlang anonymous functions
      (in the response of logging.json and services.json)
    * Add the cloudi_logger cloudi_core module for CloudI logger
      aspects_log_after configuration with functions that can stop
      CloudI execution based on log output (for test execution)
    * Add integration tests configuration to ensure CloudI execution
      stops with exit code 1 when any tests fail

2023-01-05 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix cloudi_service_monitoring assertion after fatal_timeout change
      for external service support

2022-10-12 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * CloudI version 2.0.5 released

2022-10-06 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add outages text visual representation to the CloudI Service API
      nodes_status response for the tracked downtime of disconnected nodes
      (only a local view based on the local connection to a remote node)

