2022-08-13 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add percentiles output to cloudi_service_request_rate

2022-08-12 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add the cloudi_percentiles cloudi_core module

2022-08-11 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix the cloudi_service_shell terminate_kills_process feature
    * Change the default values for cloudi_service_shell arguments
      timeout_kills_process_signal and terminate_kills_process_signal
      to sigkill because it is the best cross-platform setting that
      terminates any shell

2022-08-10 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Change the minimum Haskell requirement to GHC 8.6.0

2022-08-09 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Remove cabal-install dependency for very important reasons:
        * All sandbox functionality was removed (cabal-install >= 3.4)
          without replacement functionality
          (https://github.com/haskell/cabal/issues/6445)
        * cabal-install source code releases are unable to bootstrap with
          local dependencies due to undependable releases that promote
          opaque binaries
          (https://github.com/haskell/cabal/issues/7904)
    * Manually create a Cabal sandbox without cabal-install for
      Haskell GHC compilation

2022-08-05 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Haskell support cabal-install >= 3.4 build change for
      integration tests

2022-08-04 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix service shutdown during initialization so it is not an error
      if the reason is shutdown or {shutdown, any()}
      (for both internal and external services)
    * Limit the cloudi_service_http_cowboy reuse_port argument to
      Linux and FreeBSD (to keep the argument meaning the same)
    * Haskell support with GHC >= 9.0 requires the use of
      cabal-install >= 3.4 which has removed the v1-sandbox command
      (https://github.com/haskell/cabal/issues/6445) and all
      sandbox functionality
        * cabal v2-install --lib appears unable to provide a local
          installation in a sandbox-like directory though that functionality
          may be pursued as an "env" command
          (https://github.com/haskell/cabal/issues/6481)
        * Support of GHC >= 9.0 will be blocked on cabal-install's
          ability to use local installations of libraries
        * Changes based on the current cabal-install support
          have been added for further improvement
    * Update Haskell network dependency to 3.1.2.7
    * Update Haskell zlib dependency to 0.6.3.0

2022-07-30 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add cloudi_math module with functions erfinv/1 and erfcinv/1
    * Increase default test timeout from 10 seconds to 20 seconds

2022-07-23 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix internal/external service restart tracking when
      count_process > 1 and the service configuration option
      restart_all is false (the default)
        * Fixes the CloudI Service API services_status
          uptime_restarts value
        * Ensures the max_r service configuration value is enforced
          as the maximum number of restarts for all processes
    * Improve cloudi_service_api_batch processing when the argument
      purge_on_error is true (the default) and a service
      with count_process > 1 terminates with an error
      (any restart of any process due to an error will now cause a purge)
    * Fix cloudi_service_router parameter substitution errors
      due to a mismatch between the trie:find_match2/2 functionality
      and the trie:pattern2_parse/2 functionality
        * Fix the mismatch between trie:find_match2/2 functionality and
          trie:pattern2_parse/2 functionality with the trie update
    * Add the cloudi_service_shell arguments terminate_kills_process
      and terminate_kills_process_signal for handling shell execution
      during service termination
    * Fix cloudi_service_shell use of the timeout_kills_process argument
      so a timeout does not cause service termination
    * Update key2value
    * Update trie

2022-07-16 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add cloudi_statistics describe functions and cached values

2022-07-02 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add the reuse_port argument to the cloudi_service_http_cowboy with
      the default allowing the use of count_process > 1
    * Improve the cloudi_service_request_rate log output

2022-06-25 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Change cloudi_service_request_rate to use process 0
      for processing results and add request latency log output

2022-06-18 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix cloudi_service_send async == true usage so the service
      initializes and terminates immediately
    * Remove the cloudi_math cloudi_core module
    * Add the cloudi_statistics cloudi_core module

2022-06-10 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix the fatal_exceptions service configuration option support in the
      ATS CloudI API
    * Changed the FatalError exception in the ATS CloudI API to accept a
      string parameter that is typically $mylocation for providing the
      $raise location
    * Fixed stderr exception information provided by the ATS CloudI API
    * Improve the C/C++ CloudI API unbuffered stdout/stderr use

2022-06-04 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add the fatal_exceptions service configuration option support to
      external services
      (ATS/C/C++/Go/Haskell/Java/JavaScript/OCaml/Perl/PHP/Python/Ruby
       CloudI API implementations were changed)
    * Fix CloudI Service API services_update external services validation
      so the arguments file_path, args or env are not required
      (to ensure an external service update without
       an OS process restart is allowed)

2022-05-30 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add the fatal_exceptions service configuration option with the
      default value true for whether a service restart should occur
      for unexpected exceptions that the programming language
      considers recoverable
        * internal services previously had default value true functionality
          but external services have had fatal_exceptions == false
          functionality
          (external services don't yet use the fatal_exceptions value,
           but it will be described as a backwards incompatible change
           in the next release's NEWS after external services have it
           hooked-up)
        * If fatal_exceptions is false a null response is provided
    * Add the fatal_timeout and fatal_timeout_delay service configuration
      options to cause a service restart if a service request takes
      longer than the timeout parameter
        * fatal_timeout defaults to false
        * fatal_timeout_delay defaults to 0 milliseconds
    * Improve CloudI Service API nodes_status and services_status
      to provide day information for a failure during the past year
    * Update quickrand

2022-05-14 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Update cpg
    * Update quickrand

2022-05-07 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Update uuid
    * Update quickrand

2022-04-30 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add support for the period format to the
      reconnect_start and reconnect_delay nodes configuration value
    * Add support for the period format to the
      hibernate, count_process_dynamic and rate_request_max
      service configuration options (in the period value)
    * Add support for the period format to the
      services_update timeout configuration values

2022-04-23 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add support for the period format to the
      max_t service configuration value
    * Update quickrand
    * Update erlang_term

2022-04-16 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add support for the period format to cloudi:new/1 options
      (dest_refresh_start, dest_refresh_delay, timeout_async, timeout_sync)
    * Improve cloudi_core_i_os_port
    * Update erlang_term

2022-04-09 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add the logging configuration option file_sync to delay
      calling fdatasync after a logging file line is written
      (defaults to 0 milliseconds, i.e., disabled by default)
        * Avoids the OS scheduler adjusting CPU time of processes
          by reducing hard disk use

2022-04-02 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add support for the period format in all retry_delay arguments
      (cloudi_service_funnel, cloudi_service_map_reduce,
       cloudi_service_queue, cloudi_queue)
    * Fix the C/C++ CloudI API poll timeout when either
      clock_gettime CLOCK_MONOTONIC or gettimeofday allowed the
      elapsed time to become negative
      (possible with clock_gettime CLOCK_MONOTONIC when using
       MacOS (Big Sur and Monterey at least),
       e.g. setting the system clock back)

2022-03-26 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Support the "period" timeout format in the Timeout parameters of
      cloudi and cloudi_service Erlang module functions and in
      service configuration millisecond values
      ("period" format is {pos_integer(), seconds | minutes | hours | days})
        * Anything that supports the "period" timeout format also supports the
          use of the atoms limit_max and limit_min for the value's extremes
    * Update quickrand
    * Update cpg

2022-03-20 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add the cloudi_service_router configuration arguments
      parameters_allowed_default and parameters_strict_matching_default
    * Update trie

2022-03-12 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Improve cloudi_service_router
        * Add destinations http_redirect configuration argument to
          provide a HTTP 301 redirect response
        * Fix destination configuration argument validation

2022-02-27 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Update Go CloudI API Erlang External Term Format encoding

2022-02-26 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Update Erlang External Term Format encoding used by the
      Go/Haskell/JavaScript/OCaml/Perl/PHP/Python/Ruby CloudI API
      to prepare for Erlang/OTP 26 deprecating latin1 atoms

2022-01-28 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Improve filepath normalization validation in cloudi_core configuration
      for the CloudI Service API functions services_update,
      code_path_add and code_path_remove

2022-01-15 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Simplify Erlang compiler warning options (based on Erlang/OTP 24.2)

2022-01-14 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Improve filepath normalization validation in cloudi_core configuration
      for the CloudI Service API functions services_update,
      code_path_add and code_path_remove
    * Provide {error, timeout} response in cloudi_service_api_requests
      when an invalid argument is provided (unparsable)

2022-01-13 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Update PHP integration tests threading-related comments

2022-01-12 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Remove Erlang/OTP < 22.0 compatibility

2022-01-10 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Require Erlang/OTP >= 22.0 for depending on the Erlang/OTP kernel logger
      instead of previous usage of sasl (for logging supervisor progress)
        * Remove sasl from the cloudi_core dependencies
        * Remove install_erlang_sasl_time and runtime_erlang_sasl_version
          from the CloudI Service API code_status result
    * Java CloudI API compilation now uses javac -encoding UTF-8
    * Update reltool_util
    * Update varpool

2022-01-06 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix cloudi_service_monitoring cloudi_core state use
    * Improve cloudi_core logger support for internal services
      compiled with CloudI =< 2.0.4
    * Improve cloudi_core Erlang type specifications
    * Update epgsql
    * Update hut

2021-12-30 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix service process leak when stop reason 'normal' is used

2021-12-23 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add logger compatibility with CloudI =< 2.0.4

2021-12-22 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Update logging related comment

2021-12-21 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix cloudi_service_api_requests JSON output
        * Fix the internal service module value when a string is configured
        * Improve UTF8 handling of service string data
    * Increase the queue_mode_async/queue_mode_sync logging
      configuration values in the integration tests configuration
      for slower disk writes (e.g., RAID 1 with a journaling filesystem)

2021-12-18 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add Python 3.10 compatibility to the Python/C CloudI API
    * Fix CloudI logger macro use in header files with usage of
      ?FILE instead of ?MODULE (a string instead of an atom)
        * Logging aspects had the Module parameter change to FileName
        * Logging formatters now allow either a module name atom or
          a file name string to be used in a list (with file names preferred)
          for the key value
        * Now logging output has a file extension
        * Updated the Elixir CloudILogger module
    * Fix a rare error condition in the cloudi_os_spawn Erlang port that
      would prevent cloudi_os_spawn from terminating at shutdown time

2021-12-09 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix cloudi_service_api:code_status() type

2021-12-07 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add backward-cpp fix for Linux PowerPC compilation

2021-12-06 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Use the message_queue_data off_heap spawn opt for
      the CloudI logger process to provide better performance
      when the process is in sync or overload mode

2021-12-05 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * CloudI version 2.0.4 released

2021-11-05 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add the cloudi_service_map_reduce elapsed_seconds function
    * Remove the cloudi_service_map_reduce suspend/resume functions
      to rely upon CloudI service suspend/resume functionality
      with the aspect_suspend/aspect_resume functions

2021-10-30 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Improve service update while the service is suspended with
      the service configuration option aspects_suspend set
      (aspects_suspend functions are called before the update occurs,
       if there is a pending update)

2021-10-29 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add the cloudi_service_name functions utf8/1 and utf8_forced/1
      for Erlang io formatting of a service name or service name pattern
      with ~ts as UTF-8 (to avoid erroneous interpretation as UTF-32)

2021-10-23 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix the service configuration options
      aspects_suspend and aspects_resume so the aspect function
      execution is delayed until the current service request is done
      (if the service is resumed before the current service request
       is done, neither the aspects_suspend functions or
       the aspects_resume functions will execute)
        * Before the fix, execution could fail to update the
          service's state, with the problem being more common with the
          aspects_suspend functions
    * Force all service name and service name patterns to be
      byte strings (in UTF8) to reduce cpg/trie memory usage
        * Previously external services already had this limitation,
          now it applies to internal services and configuration parameters
    * Reduce memory use in the external service Erlang process
    * Update trie

2021-10-16 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add the async argument to cloudi_service_send for
      turning off response-handling features

2021-10-15 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix cloudi_service_api_batch:queue_clear and
      cloudi_service_api_batch:services_restart usage when
      queue_dependencies configuration prevents queue execution

2021-09-10 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix CloudI Service API nodes_set discovery ec2
      environment variable substitution
    * Fix README integration-tests configure information

2021-09-02 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add build_cloudi_version to the CloudI Service API
      code_status output for the current git commit hash
      (releases will have the same value as runtime_cloudi_version)
    * Update jinterface

2021-08-30 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add boost::stacktrace support for the C++ CloudI API as a
      cross-platform dependency to use instead of booster
      (backward-cpp is still preferred on Linux)
    * Update README dependency package information

2021-08-27 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Improve C/C++ CloudI API backtrace configure check

2021-08-26 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add the validate_response argument to
      cloudi_service_cron and cloudi_service_send for more
      explicit validation that is configurable
    * Add cloudi_service_shell:validate_response/2
      for default validate_response argument use in
      cloudi_service_cron and cloudi_service_send

2021-08-25 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add cloudi_service_send for service request sends that must
      occur based on service configuration argument data
      (e.g., for cloudi_service_api_batch or configuration file use)
    * Remove cloudi_service_filesystem notify functions because
      they were assuming only 1 process existed
    * Fix cloudi_service_filesystem notify_one/notify_all so a
      single pattern matching a single path
      causes a single notification
      (previously an exact pattern for a GET method would affect
       the other methods present causing a notification for each method)

2021-08-24 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add additional cloudi_ip_address:patterns/1 tests

2021-08-19 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Add cloudi_ip_address:patterns/1 for creating service name patterns
      that match IP addresses based on a CIDR notation string

2021-08-18 Michael Truog   <mjtruog at protonmail dot com>

    * Fix cloudi_ip_address so it uses standard formatting
      (no fixed size is possible due to past support of octal in IPv4)
    * Change cloudi_service_tcp and cloudi_service_udp RequestInfo for
      consistency with HTTP services
      (e.g., source-address is used instead of source_address)
    * Change cloudi_service_http_cowboy, cloudi_service_http_cowboy1 and
      cloudi_service_http_elli by removing RequestInfo
      "peer" and "peer-port" (to rely on "source-address" and "source-port")
    * Change cloudi_service_http_client to ignore RequestInfo with
      "peer" or "peer-port"

